chapters.title: TV personality Phil McGraw- best known as "Dr. Phil"
The Dr. Phil case is an example of a common Big Pharma tactic known as "disease awareness."
In turn, they build the base of patients who take a drug company's medications.
Clearly, the drugmaker doesn't have an interest in giving the public objective information about all the different treatments available for diabetes
the kind of information that can help people make evidence-based choices about the harms, benefits, and trade-offs of various therapies.
